OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCanada offers up to $40bn  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fto compensate indigenous   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fchildren                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Canada has pledged up to C$40bn ($31bn;
OL,6, #23.6bn) in compensation for indigenous
OL,7, children and families who suffered     
OL,8, discrimination while in foster care.   
OL,10,FIn September, a top court upheld a 2016
OL,11,Fruling that the government underfunded 
OL,12,FFirst Nations services compared with   
OL,13,Fthose for non-indigenous children.     
OL,15,FIt ordered C$40,000 ($31,350; #23,340) 
OL,16,Fpayouts to each child who was in the   
OL,17,Fon-reserve welfare system after 2006.  
OL,19,FThe government initially said it would 
OL,20,Fappeal the verdict.                    
